---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----- (* Define the module *)   \* The original 'module' name was changed to avoid confusion. *\    (**************************************************************************)     CONSTANTS Goal, Jug <-, MCJug(), Capacity  <-)  /(* You need a function here that returns capacity based on jugs chosen by user or predefined in another module*)   \* The original 'module' name was changed to avoid confusion. *\    (**************************************************************************)
Spec == (* Specification *)       [](\E x, y : Jug |-> DieHarder[x + Capacity(y), Goal])  /(* This is the same as in module diehard but with capacity replaced by MCCapcity*)   \* The original 'module' name was changed to avoid confusion. *\
TypeOK == (* Type invariant *)    [](\A x : Jug |-> Capacity(x) IN NATURALS /\{0\} )  //(* A constant capacity should be in natural numbers excluding zero*)   \* The original 'module' name was changed to avoid confusion. *\
NotSolved == (* Additional invariant *) [](\A x : Jug |-> DieHarder[x, Goal] /= TRUE)    %%(* A jug that is not solved yet in the diehard problem*)   \* The original 'module' name was changed to avoid confusion. *\
=============================================================================  (* Separator *)  (**************************************************************************)\    === TLC Configuration === \(*\ Definition of constants for configuration file\)    CONSTANTS Goal = <4>, Jug=<MCJug()>  /(* The goal and jug are defined as in the problem statement*)   \* You need to define MCJugs elsewhere. *\
====